Discussion occurred in this thread http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Confluence+4.0+Editor+-+Customer+Feedback?focusedCommentId=285840857#comment-285840857

In short, I cannot simply enter an opening bracket, type a new or extant page name, then type the closing bracket and create a link.

To replicate, create a page with the following:

{noformat}
h1. Title

{excerpt}
This is a test.
{excerpt}
{noformat}

The page will render with very little whitespace between the heading and line. Add another line underneath it like...

{noformat}
h1. Title

{excerpt}
This is a test.
{excerpt}

This is also a test.
{noformat}

... and the page will render properly.

To replicate:

Create a page with this content:

{noformat}
{excerpt}
This is a test.
{excerpt}

Another line.
{noformat}

When saving the page, the space between the two lines will be removed.

Add a title to the top of the page like so:

{noformat}
h2. This is a title.

{excerpt}
This is a test.
{excerpt}

Another line.
{noformat}

... and the gap will render properly.

Verified in Safari and Firefox.

