Add page from template with headers and text boxes generates non standard compliant HTML. The header id has spaces in the name. From the [HTML definition|http://www.w3.org/TR/html401/types.html#type-name]:
{quote}
ID and NAME tokens must begin with a letter ([A-Za-z]) and may be followed by any number of letters, digits ([0-9]), hyphens ("-"), underscores ("_"), colons (":"), and periods (".").
{quote}

That can generate problems for some customers.

For example i used this template:
{code}
h4. Text box: @textbox|textarea(1,80)@
{code}

When creating a page from a template, I get the non-standard HTML (see screeshot).

