When viewing an old version of a page, e.g. https://confluence.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=196247 at the top appears a yellow hint 
{quote} Sie zeigen eine alte Version (v. /display/DISC/German_DE+Translation) dieser Seite an. 
Unterschiede anzeigen ·  Seitenhistorie anzeigen
<< Vorherige Version anzeigen  -- Sie zeigen die aktuelle Version dieser Seite an. (v. 6) --  Nächste Version anzeigen >> {quote}

which is obviously incorrect - how could I view an old version (1st line) AND view the current version (last line) at the same time? I guess, the last line shall mean "you're currently viewing version 6".

Moreover, I do not see the point of the block "v. <pagename>" in line 1. I would understand "v. <version>" but this would double the last line?! 

The text displayed in an older version, from around 1 year ago, was really useful: There was a hint telling me which version I was currently viewing AND there was a link "show latest version" or the like. This was clear and made sense and enabled me to jump to lastest version with only 1 click. Hope you wanna have a look at the older versions :)

